    stem: `Will, 13 years old, is brought in for the assessment of back pain by his mother. When you want to examine him, he asks if the examination can be carried out in the absence of his mother as he feels embarrassed to take off his clothes in front of her. When alone in the room with you, he confides that he has been molested by his stepfather, who married his mother two years ago. Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
