    stem: `You are assessing a 15-year-old girl for low weight. She has a body mass index (BMI) of 15. She hates food because she thinks it makes her fat. She avoids eating as long as she can, but when she is urged to eat due to hunger, she induces vomiting or uses laxatives to get rid of it. During the interview, you ask if she participates in any activity of her interest. She replies: 'Why should I? What does the entire world mean? Nothing.' Which of the following is more likely to be elicited from the rest of the history?`,
