    topic: "Psychiatry",
    subtopic: "Delirium in dialysis patients",
    stem: `A 73-year-old woman with end-stage renal disease (ESRD), who has been well-controlled on routine peritoneal dialysis and has been coping well thus far, suddenly declines to have her dialysis session today. On examination, she is found to have a temperature of 38.3°C and mild tenderness in her upper abdomen. Which of the following could be the most likely additional finding in this patient?`,
