    stem: `An 82-year-old man male presents to the emergency department with a knife in his hand. He claims that he hears voices saying his neighbours want to kill him and he should kill them before they kill him. You, as the attending physician, manage to de-escalate him and convince him to surrender his knife verbally. Which one of the following would be the next best step in management?`,
