    correctAnswer: "A",
    explanation: `Feminising hormone therapy involves the use of oestradiol and spironolactone. Decreased libido is one of the early effects that occurs soon after starting feminising hormone therapy. The effects of feminising hormones develop over time, with various changes occurring at different timeframes. Oestradiol causes reduction in muscle mass and testicular volume, but voice feminisation typically takes longer than 6 to 12 months. Option C is incorrect because oily skin is not a typical effect, and voice changes take longer. Option D describes effects that are not characteristic of feminising hormone therapy in this context. Option E incorrectly attributes voice feminisation to oestrogen alone and mischaracterizes the timeline and mechanism.`,
