    stem: `Jane, 32 years old, gave birth to her child three days ago and has been in the ward since. On the second day, she went to the nurses and told them that she was very worried and afraid about her child and needed to keep her safe in the room. Last night, she was seen walking around and moving objects. She sprayed an insecticide on the floor to get rid of imaginary bugs. On examination, she is agitated with a heart rate of 110 bpm, respiratory rate of 22 breaths per minute and temperature of 37.5°C. Which one of the following is the most important initial step in management?`,
