    stem: `A man brings his wife to your practice for a consultation because he has been excessively cleaning the house and drinking alcohol in the past five days. She has fought with him a lot and flirted with his friends. During the consultation, she initially is flirtatious but then becomes angry and starts talking to you very rudely. According to her husband, she was previously quite normal. Which one of the following is the next best step in management?`,
