    stem: `Anne is a 65-year-old part-time nurse who has been reported for evaluation by her colleagues. For the past 12 months, she has been increasingly apathetic and has lost interest in her daily activities, including gardening, which she has been doing for the past 40 years. Recently, she has started accusing her colleagues of stealing things from the ward whenever something is lost. During the interview, she has a flat affect and reduced eye contact. She can answer simple questions but is unable to process more complex ideas. She denies hallucinations, falls or movement disorders. Which one of the following could be the most likely diagnosis?`,
