    explanation: `Exposure and response prevention (ERP) is an important and specific behaviour therapy for OCD. In ERP, situations the patient perceives as threatening are ranked, and the patient is systematically exposed to gradually increasing intensity symptom triggers while being taught to suppress their usual ritualised response. This promotes unlearning of the strong link between having an urge and giving in to it. Option A (Insight-oriented psychotherapy) is not effective for OCD as patients already have adequate insight into their condition. Option B is incorrect because explaining the mechanism does not help—the problem is the irresistible urge itself, not lack of awareness. Option D (Psychoanalytic therapy) has not proved significantly effective for OCD. Option E (Dialectic therapy) is the treatment of choice for borderline personality disorder, not OCD.`,
