    subtopic: "Formal thought disorders - Circumstantiality",
    stem: `While taking a history from a patient in a psychiatry ward, you ask him if there is any history of mental illnesses in the family. He answers: 'Good question. Now that you've asked, I must tell you something. Whales are good creatures. We take their oil and use it to light the world. My father hunted whales, and my grandpa did, too. The business runs in the family; of course, we are all sane and sound. Do you think we are crazy?' Which one of the following is present in this patient's speech?`,
