    stem: `A 76-year-old man is brought to your clinic by his son because of a progressive decline in memory for the past 18 months, as well as weakness of his upper and lower limbs and deterioration of motor function. On examination, right hemiparesis is evident. Which one of the following could be the most likely diagnosis?`,
